imdb.plot outline: Documentary series Kmeny (Tribes), based on the novel Kmeny from 2011, takes viewers to the places where they have probably never been before. Into communities that deliberately defines themselves from the others. Each episode tries to capture engagingly, visually and in the most notable way the typical subcultural activities and partial rituals. Sixteen twenty-six minutes lasting episodes recorded by different directors are broadcasted by Czech Television and are also available for online viewing on kmeny.tv.
imdb.title: Kmeny
plot: Documentary series _Kmeny_ (qv) (Tribes), based on the novel _Kmeny_ (qv) from 2011, takes viewers to the places where they have probably never been before. Into communities that deliberately defines themselves from the others. Each episode tries to capture engagingly, visually and in the most notable way the typical subcultural activities and partial rituals. Sixteen twenty-six minutes lasting episodes recorded by different directors are broadcasted by Czech Television and are also available for online viewing on kmeny.tv.

_Kmeny_ (qv) (Tribes), co-produced documentary series, explores contemporary urban subcultures. The cycle has sixteen episodes, which introduces the functioning of various communities from hipsters, through hackers, hooligans to thrash metalheads.
